Okay, how was this handled *before* the patch?  Looking back, `remove_pfn_range_from_zone` *used to* call `clear_zone_contiguous(zone)` which sets `zone->contiguous = false` *before* it poisoned the pages! So the poisoning happened *after* the contiguity check was explicitly invalidated.  Looks like that sequence is what prevented this problem, and that is why the previous implementation was safer! This needs further investigation.


